<heading id="DA2B1510FFFECE2EFF77FF4FDA1C3C97" bold="true" box="[136,335,158,185]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFFECE2EFF77FF4FDA1C3C97" bold="true" box="[136,335,158,185]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">
Group 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFFECE2EFF1DFF4EDA1C3C97" baseAuthorityName="Keyserling" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[226,335,159,185]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFFECE2EFF1DFF4EDA1C3C97" bold="true" box="[226,335,159,185]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C9C6F1F7FFFECE2EFF77FF39D9983F5E" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8163A27CFFFECE2EFF77FF39DA6F3E65" blockId="115.[136,778,232,880]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFFECE2EFF77FF39DA513D2C" bold="true" box="[136,258,232,258]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of the group 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFFECE2EFE0EFF38D90A3D2C" baseAuthorityName="Keyserling" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[497,601,233,258]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFFECE2EFE0EFF38D90A3D2C" box="[497,601,233,258]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are recognized by the following combination of characters: Small total length; patterns of coloration on legs or palpal articles present; embolus with three keels; BTA developed (except on 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFFECE2EFF4FFEAADA1C3DBA" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1920" box="[176,335,379,405]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paranensis">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFFECE2EFF4FFEAADA1C3DBA" box="[176,335,379,405]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">A. paranensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); serrated area on prolateral embolus large, densely covered by relatively large denticles. Females are recognized by the spermathecae having two bilobed receptacles, with outer lobes higher than inner lobes; pore distribution reaching 75% of apical portion on each receptacle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8163A27CFFFECE2EFF42FD87D9983F5E" blockId="115.[136,778,232,880]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFFECE2EFF42FD87DAD83E5E" bold="true" box="[189,395,598,624]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Species included.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFFECE2EFE6BFD87DB9E3EBB" authority="(Keyserling, 1891)" baseAuthorityName="Keyserling" baseAuthorityYear="1891" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
